MySQL querries
.select - selects data from database 
.select distinct 
    .returns only distinct (different) values; values that are not duplicates of each other 
.where 
    .filters records; extracts those records that fulfill a specified condition 

Primary key
    .the constraint uniquely identifying each record in a table 
    .must contain UNIQUE values, and cannot contain NULL values
    .can only be one in a table
        .can consist of single or multiple columns(fields)
    .found in the referenced/ parent table 



Foreign key
    .used to prevent actions that would destroy links between tables 
    >its a field/ collection of fields in one table that refers to the PRIMARY KEY in another table 
    .found in the child table 